				Trolls eat gnomes and elves. No, in roleplay you would rarely see such an allience HOWEVER, to you who complain about &quot;cross-teamers&quot; there are things called allience of friendship. Maybe an orge was being chased down by some guards and about to die when a merciful paladin rooted the guards in secret and allowed the troll to escape. This would be grounds to form a Friendship Allience. Meaning they won't kill eachother because they are friends to one another and are their own bosses. I play on Vallon Zek and I see cross teaming as a minor problem that lay forth as The Prophets but aside from that, it's almost none existent.<BR>
<BR>
If this gnome gets suspended or banned I feel as though I must shoot the guide who does it. NO GMs should NOT be allowed the right to EVER in ANYCASE interfear with possible RP situations and being a rogue, this was entitled an RP action of theft. Bad bad GM, leave the gnome alone. If I see him, I'll give him a ravenscale piece. Bwahahaha!<BR>
<BR>
Yes, GMs should permit the ability for others characters to attack a specific character in certain cases but this should not be abused on PK servers if implimented by some one on the inside helping the PKer win loads of cash off twinks (Authorizing a 12+ to kill a level 1 twink who has alot of money on him).<BR>
