	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				First of all, why was a 6th level grouped with those two hgher levels?  He's not getting any exp, so he SHOULD get something to compensate for that.  Also, it's a freaking Mino Axe, they cost 5pp and are not difficult to get.  The higher levels should have let him have it.<BR>
Now, I agree with the aforementioned need for having loot rules in a party.  Any party I'm in it's the first thing I ask.  We usually set do ahead of time what items we need to roll for.  If they guy ahead of my loots a fine steel, and I loot a rusty, I'm not going to make him roll for his fine steel.<BR>
As far as GMs/Guides, there are times when we need them to intervine BECAUSE we cannont avenge ourselves.  I was in a party in Mistmoor once where we had killed a gargoyle with an eye on it.  It was one of the things we'd agreed to roll on, and while we were rolling for it, this paladin (of all things!) that had been hanging out by us but not in our party comes over and loots it, and zones out.  He'd been dumb and commented about it to the whole zone before leaving, so half the people in the zone took screenshots and petitioned.  We got our eye back, and he got a warning.  i wouldn've been just as happy to kill him and make him lose some EXP, but we CAN'T.  So we need the Guides unless they come up with something better.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
