			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I think that in this case, he was just using roleplaying as an excuse. As people have mentioned before, he could of asked the others in the group if they wanted it and rolled, if he wanted to keep a good reputation. Just because you are &quot;roleplaying&quot; doesn't give you the right to ninja-loot. Some people said that he should get compensation for grouping with higher level people, who he wouldn't get experience with, but this just makes me think that he went into the group specifically to take the loot. There is a possibility that this guy was RPing; if so, then he needs to learn that going about it in this way will just lead to no-one wanting to group with him because he'll be considered so untrustworthy. This is like the times when people used to loot others' corpses, claiming it was &quot;roleplaying&quot;, because the person was another race/evil. Although this may be true in a RP sense, people were just ruining others' gaming experiences to get phat l00t fo themselves, very similar to this occurance (although not many people consider a mino axe phat l00t :). Basically, you can do anything, as long as it doesn't infringe upon other people's enjoyment of the game, because once you cross that point, other people will not like you, and you will and should be reported.
				</font>
			</td>

