				  What we have here is a tale told by 3 idiots. It's a mino axe, why should a 17 warrior care, and the druid can't use it anyways, therefore give it to the newbie. However, the other players were greedy, and threw a little tantrum, in response the thief ran off, and then refused to listen to the guide. Ok, he was roleplaying, so lets roleplay, you ever tell a policeman off? There are consequences for such actions, and often times the result may lead to broken ribs, which is beyond what the law allows, however, judges tend to be more agreeable to the officers side of the story than the criminals side. So if you want to roleplay, fine, just remember that guides and gm's should be allowed to roleplay as well.
